# TypeScript Frontend Standards

## Typing

- Enable `strict` mode in tsconfig (already configured).
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` and narrow with type guards when the type is uncertain.
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes.
- Use explicit return types on exported functions.

## Project Structure

```
src/
  main.ts          # barba.js init and global setup
  transitions/     # transition modules (one per file)
  views/           # view hook modules (one per namespace)
  utils/           # shared helpers
  style.css        # global styles
```

## Patterns

- Use ES module imports; no CommonJS (`require`).
- Prefer `const` over `let`; never use `var`.
- Use `async/await` over raw Promises where possible.
- Keep functions small and single-purpose.
- Co-locate related types with their module.

## Vite Specifics

- Use `import.meta.env` for environment variables (not `process.env`).
- Static assets in `public/` are served at root path.
- Use `import` for assets you want processed by Vite (images, SVGs in `src/`).

## DOM Interaction

- Use `document.querySelector` with type parameters: `document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.selector')`.
- Prefer data attributes (`data-*`) over class-based selectors for JS hooks.
- Avoid direct DOM manipulation when barba handles container replacement; use barba lifecycle hooks.
